issue.title: [RGen] Add a validator for the Export<Method> attribute.
issue.body:
This allows to validate attributes that have the Method flag, the validator checks the following:

1. Async and Event flags cannot be combined.
2. ResultType is only allowed in Async methods.
3. ResultTypeName is only allowed in Async methods.
4. Methodname is only allowed is Async methods.
5. PostNonResultSnipped is only allows in Async methods.
6. StrongDelegateType is not set.
7. StrongDelegateName is not set.
8. StrongDictionaryKeyClass is not set.
9. EventArgsName is only allowed in Event methods.
10. EventArgsType is only allowed in Event methods.

This validator will later be used to validate the export data in a metod struct.

pull_request.title: feat: Add ConnectionDefinition support to registration utilities
pull_request.body:
This PR adds support for ConnectionDefinition entities in the MeshKit registration system. Previously, when importing models that contained connection definitions, these entities were being silently ignored because the registration pipeline didn't know how to handle them.

## What was broken

The main issue was in `utils/utils.go` - the `FindEntityType` function was missing a case for `connections.meshery.io`, so it couldn't identify connection definition files. This meant connection definitions were being skipped during model import.

## What I fixed

- Added the missing `connections.meshery.io` case to `FindEntityType` in `utils/utils.go`
- Made `getEntity` public as `GetEntity` in `models/registration/utils.go` so it can be tested
- Updated `PackagingUnit` in `models/registration/register.go` to include connections and handle their registration
- Added connection file processing in `models/registration/dir.go` 
- Added connection support to the database schema in `models/meshmodel/registry/registry.go`
- Created the `ConnectionDefinition` type in `models/meshmodel/core/v1beta1/connection.go`
- Added `ConnectionSchemaVersion` constant in the corev1beta1 package

Based on reviewer feedback, I've made the following adjustments:
- Reverted `GetEntity` back to unexported `getEntity` since it's not used outside the package
- Moved `ConnectionSchemaVersion` constant to the corev1beta1 package
- Removed unnecessary changes to OPA and OCI files that were unrelated to the ConnectionDefinition task
- Kept only the essential changes needed for ConnectionDefinition support

## Testing

I tested this with a sample ConnectionDefinition JSON file. The pipeline now works correctly:
- `FindEntityType` properly identifies connection definition files
- `getEntity` parses them into the right type
- The registration process handles them end-to-end

Before this fix, connection definitions were just being ignored. Now the registry can properly handle all entity types: components, relationships, and connections.

Related to #762

---

**Notes for Reviewers**
- [Signed commits](CONTRIBUTING.md)
- [x] Yes, I signed my commits.

pull_request.title: feat: Add ConnectionDefinition support to registration utilities
pull_request.body:
This PR adds support for ConnectionDefinition entities in the MeshKit registration system. Previously, when importing models that contained connection definitions, these entities were being silently ignored because the registration pipeline didn't know how to handle them.

## What was broken

The main issue was in `utils/utils.go` - the `FindEntityType` function was missing a case for `connections.meshery.io`, so it couldn't identify connection definition files. This meant connection definitions were being skipped during model import.

## What I fixed

- Added the missing `connections.meshery.io` case to `FindEntityType` in `utils/utils.go`
- Made `getEntity` public as `GetEntity` in `models/registration/utils.go` so it can be tested
- Updated `PackagingUnit` in `models/registration/register.go` to include connections and handle their registration
- Added connection file processing in `models/registration/dir.go` 
- Added connection support to the database schema in `models/meshmodel/registry/registry.go`
- Created the `ConnectionDefinition` type in `models/meshmodel/core/v1beta1/connection.go`
- Added `ConnectionSchemaVersion` constant in the corev1beta1 package

Based on reviewer feedback, I've made the following adjustments:
- Reverted `GetEntity` back to unexported `getEntity` since it's not used outside the package
- Moved `ConnectionSchemaVersion` constant to the corev1beta1 package
- Removed unnecessary changes to OPA and OCI files that were unrelated to the ConnectionDefinition task
- Kept only the essential changes needed for ConnectionDefinition support

## Testing

I tested this with a sample ConnectionDefinition JSON file. The pipeline now works correctly:
- `FindEntityType` properly identifies connection definition files
- `getEntity` parses them into the right type
- The registration process handles them end-to-end

Before this fix, connection definitions were just being ignored. Now the registry can properly handle all entity types: components, relationships, and connections.

Related to #762

---

**Notes for Reviewers**
- [Signed commits](CONTRIBUTING.md)
- [x] Yes, I signed my commits.

commits.message:
feat(ux): show selected task details in Context panel

Implements the context panel feature, allowing users to select a task and view its detailed information.

- Adds a `renderContextPanel` function to display task details (name, id, duration, dependencies, timings, slack, critical status) in the right-hand sidebar.
- Updates click handlers in the timeline and dependency graph to support single-task selection, which populates the context panel.
- Modifies the selection logic (`updateSelBadge`) to call the new rendering function whenever the selection changes.
- Implements keyboard navigation:
  - Makes the timeline and graph views focusable via `tabindex`.
  - Scopes arrow key listeners (`Up`/`Down`) to these views for task navigation.
  - Implements an `Enter` key handler to move focus from a selected task to the context panel.
- Wires up action buttons (Edit, Duplicate, Activate/Deactivate, Delete) in the context panel to their corresponding functions in the state manager.

Merge pull request #41 from Machimelofafa/feat/context-panel-binding

pull_request.title: Add comprehensive development infrastructure and orchestration system
pull_request.body:
## Summary

• **Development Infrastructure**: Added complete CLAUDE.md with development commands, architecture overview, and project configuration details
• **Budget Allocation System**: Implemented time-based test optimization with calibration phase, Secretary Problem mathematics for infinite domains, and proportional scaling
• **Test Orchestration**: Added two-phase execution system (calibration + execution) with cardinality-aware attempt allocation
• **CLI Integration**: Added proper package entry point via __main__.py for `python -m minigun` execution
• **Documentation**: Added comprehensive cardinality system documentation with examples and usage patterns
• **Development Workflow**: Added rule2hook configuration for automated development process improvements

This infrastructure enables sophisticated test optimization, comprehensive development tooling, and professional project management while maintaining backward compatibility.

## Test plan

- [x] All existing tests pass with new infrastructure
- [x] CLI entry point works correctly via __main__.py  
- [x] Pre-commit hooks validate all changes
- [x] Coverage maintained at acceptable levels for infrastructure commit
- [x] Budget allocation system integrates with existing test framework
- [x] Documentation is comprehensive and accurate
